'''Ben van Beneden''' is the director of the [[Rubenshuis]] (Rubens House), the former home and studio of [[Peter Paul Rubens]] in Antwerp, and an authority on the art of Rubens.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.codart.nl/guide/curators/ben-van-beneden/|title=Ben van Beneden -|work=CODART|access-date=2017-10-01|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://artdependence.com/issue/april-2015/article/rubens-in-private-an-interview-with-ben-van-beneden-director-of-rubenshuis-antwerp|title=Rubens in Private – an interview with Ben van Beneden, director of Rubenshuis Antwerp|work=www.artdependence.com|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2017/britains-lost-masterpieces-rubens|title=BBC -  BBC Four’s Britain’s Lost Masterpieces discovers a missing Rubens masterpiece - Media Centre|website=www.bbc.co.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thamesandhudson.com/authors/ben-van-beneden-63780|title=Ben van Beneden|website=thamesandhudson.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2017-10-01}}</ref>

